      "message": "Ok, added a comment.  Also, I noticed that the tests weren\u0027t verifying individual build step results, so I added that, which led me to discover that the timeout for TestBuild/timeout was so short that the subprocess wasn\u0027t even getting started, which in turn revealed a bug in the log_parser logic which caused the subprocess not to be killed when the timeout was hit under certain circumstances (running a Bash script, as opposed to a regular command or a Python script).  Fixed the bug and added a log_parser test which fails before and succeeds after the fix.  I also noticed that log_parser isn\u0027t doing any testing to verify that the correct log output is making it to the correct step(s).  I think that\u0027ll be a more difficult thing to test, given how it\u0027s handled in the framework, so I\u0027m saving it for a later CL.",
